Nigerian NPDC Has 350 Million Barrel Oil Reserves, Guardian Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-09-15T08:28:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/nigeria-s-oil-explorer-expects-output-to-reach-250-000-barrels-in-3-years.html
Nigerian Petroleum Development Co.,
the exploration unit of the state-owned oil company, has 350
million barrels of crude reserves, the Guardian newspaper
reported, citing Managing Director Abiye Membere.  The exploration arm, also known as NPDC, currently pumps
102,000 barrels of crude and condensate a day and plans to raise
output to 265,000 barrels a day within four years, the Lagos-
based newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisha Bala-Gbogbo in Abuja at 
 ebalagbogbo@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dulue Mbachu at 
 dmbachu@bloomberg.net  